# open-interpreter — Setup Guide

## Requirements

- Python 3.14 (or 3.10+)
- Groq API key (free tier)
- Windows 10/11

## Installation

```cmd
pip install open-interpreter
```

## Configuration

Create a `.env` file in your project directory:

```
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
```

## Agent Script

Create `agent.py`:

```python
from interpreter import interpreter
import os
from dotenv import load_dotenv

load_dotenv()

interpreter.llm.model = "groq/llama-3.3-70b-versatile"
interpreter.llm.api_key = os.getenv("GROQ_API_KEY")
interpreter.auto_run = True

interpreter.chat("Go to https://books.toscrape.com. Find the book called 'Soumission' and note its price and star rating. Then navigate to the Mystery category and find the most expensive book. Report the title, price, and star rating of the most expensive Mystery book.")
```

## Running

```cmd
python agent.py
```

## Notes

- No database required
- No Docker required
- No browser window opens — agent writes and executes Python code directly
- Free Groq API tier is sufficient
- Very low token consumption compared to visual browser agents
